summary: Fast Facts- Joined New York Life at the age of 25- Promoted to management after two and a half years- Promoted to Managing Partner at the age 32- Managing Partner of New York Life in Connecticut and led the office to the #2 GPA in 2004 and the #1 GPA in the country in 2005.(GPA is the overall ranking of 120 general offices based on recruiting, retention, growth of agents, increase in first year commissions, and increase in commissions of people in their first 4 years, and paid life cases).- More than doubled the first year commission in the first 4 years.     - Was promoted to Managing Partner of New York Life in Orange County and Long Beach offices in 2007 and led the office to the 10th highest GPA in the country in 2007 and 7th highest GPA in 2008, 11th in 2009 and 9th in 2010.- In 2008, the office was awarded the Recruiting and Management Development Awards for the Pacific Zone and three national trophies (the National Senior Vice President's Award of Excellence, the Life Case Rate, and the Investment Annuity Awards).- In 2009 the office was awarded the National Case Rate Trophy and Mr. Mussehl was, for the 3rd time named a member of the Partners Round Table.- In 2010 the office had the #2 GPA in the Pacific Zone and #9 in the Entire company.- In 5 years he doubled in first year commissions of the office to over 6 million and grew the new organization (agents in years 0-3) from less than 200,000 to nearly 3 million dollars.  - The offices' news annual life premium grew from 10 million to over 50 million during management - The office's paid life cases grew from 1400 to over 5000 during his time as Managing Partner.4 Billion dollars assets under management under his supervision 400 million dollars in annual revenue - Retired in August 2012.
